<paragraph id="821F6915FF8F242CFF621ABFFE4D9EB2" blockId="15.[151,1437,616,1342]" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">
<keyLead id="3951CA20FF8F242CFF621ABFFE4D9EB2" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">
5 Head and Abd III–IV with lateral spots (
<figureCitation id="1A9B7590FF8F242CFDAC1ABFFD1C9ECC" box="[601,658,909,931]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[164,1424,182,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[164,1424,181,1837]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2A–B. Acanthocyrtus necropolitanus sp. nov., habitus of specimens fixed in ethanol (lateral view): A, specimen with weak pigments on trunk lateral; B, pigments absent on trunk lateral. Scale bars: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410908" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410908/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); labral inner papillae conical, outer papillae reduced to a small rounded projection (
<figureCitation id="1A9B7590FF8F242CFF1C1A98FEBA9EAF" box="[233,308,938,960]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1788,1812]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,181,1764]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[151,1436,181,1764]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3A–F. Acanthocyrtus necropolitanus sp. nov., antennae and dorsal head; A, apex of left Ant IV (dorsal view); B, Ant III distally (lateral view); C, chaetotaxy (mac and elongated sens) of left Ant III–I (dorsal view, from left to right), respectively; D, chaetotaxy of clypeus and prelabrum; E, labral papillae (ventral view); F, head dorsal chaetotaxy and eyes (dorsal view, left side)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6412858" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6412858/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
); labial papilla E 
<emphasis id="B0D4B507FF8F242CFE291A98FE729ED0" bold="true" box="[476,508,938,959]" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">l.p.</emphasis>
surpass the base of 
<emphasis id="B0D4B507FF8F242CFD481A98FD6F9ED0" bold="true" box="[701,737,938,959]" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">a.a.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="1A9B7590FF8F242CFD1B1A98FCB29EAF" box="[750,828,938,960]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1491,1515]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,464,1468]" captionTargetId="figure-216@5.[151,1436,453,1468]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4A–D. Acanthocyrtus necropolitanus sp. nov., ventral head (right side); A, labial papillae E (right side); B, maxillary palp and sublobal plate (right side); C, basomedian and basolateral labial fields and proximal chaetae; D, complete postlabial chaetotaxy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410921/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
); manubrium ventro-distally with 3 inner chaetae (
<figureCitation id="1A9B7590FF8F242CFAD61A98FAE29EAF" box="[1315,1388,938,960]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1378,1402]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,186,1347]" captionTargetId="figure-19@8.[151,1436,181,1354]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7A–E. Acanthocyrtus necropolitanus sp. nov., abdominal appendages; A, collophore (lateral view); B, distal manubrium (ventral view); C, manubrial plate (dorsal view), arrow indicates chaeta present or absent; D, dens spines chaetotaxy (dorsal view), E, distal dens and mucro (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410948/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
) 
<taxonomicName id="45A01296FF8F242CFA7D1A99FEFF9EB2" authority="Cipola &amp; Greenslade, 2022" authorityName="Cipola &amp; Greenslade" authorityYear="2022" class="Collembola" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Acanthocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Entomobryomorpha" pageId="15" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="necropolitanus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B0D4B507FF8F242CFA7D1A99FEFF9EB2" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">A. necropolitanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B0D4B507FF8F242CFE821AFAFE4D9EB2" bold="true" box="[375,451,968,989]" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="ABE7087CFF8F242CFE821AFAFE4D9EB2" box="[375,451,968,989]" pageId="15" pageNumber="356" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="821F6915FF8F242CFF621AD7FA12995A" blockId="15.[151,1437,616,1342]" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">
<keyLead id="3951CA20FF8F242CFF621AD7FA12995A" pageId="15" pageNumber="356">
- Head and trunk depigmented (
